article.headline: NDSU 85, Wisconsin-Green Bay 73
article.story: FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- Wisconsin native Mike Nelson scored 29 points to lead North Dakota State to an 85-73 victory over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Saturday. It was the 10th straight home win for the Bison (3-2), who won 12 of 13 games here a year ago. Nelson scored 21 points in the first half, on 9-of-12 shooting from the field. The 6-foot-4 sophomore was 3 of 5 from 3-point range. Ryan Evanochko topped the Phoenix (1-4) with 20 points, 18 in the second half. NDSU, which led by as much as 25 points, hung on to win without point guard Ben Woodside, who sprained his ankle late in the first half. The Bison led 41-24 at halftime. The closest margin in the second half was nine points, when Evanochko's layup pulled the Phoenix within 73-64 with 2:27 showing. NDSU's biggest lead was 31-6 after a 3-pointer by Nelson with 7:41 remaining in the first half.
